A lane of broken markers forks and rejoins in confusing angles around fallen lintels. old chains ring once and go still, and every gust carries the dry taste of old tomb air from somewhere deeper in the city.

No scavengers linger here; the chamber is held as a lethal dueling ground, untouched by lesser wanderers.~
